create_modified_sequence[source]

create_modified_sequence(df_items:Tuple, translate_mod_dict:dict=None, mod_sep='()')

Translate (sequence, mods, mod_sites) into a modified sequence. Used by df.apply(). For example, ('ABCDEFG','Mod1@A;Mod2@E','1;5')->_A[Mod1@A]BCDE[Mod2@E]FG_. Args: df_items (List): must be (sequence, mods, mod_sites) translate_mod_dict (dict): A dict to map alpha modification names to other software mod_sep (str): '[]' or '()', default '()'
